    {
      "id": "uI9bJKtKJHtNw7Zivisa5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -123.05975816232194,
      "y": 259.07529007221484,
      "width": 613.4505615234375,
      "height": 166.40839540047776,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2c",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1191172932,
      "version": 519,
      "versionNonce": 554827117,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769964384280,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Users -\nEach user connects to one server\nholding Long polling/WebSocket\nRequest for Bi-Directional messaging ",
      "fontSize": 33.28167908009555,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Users -\nEach user connects to one server\nholding Long polling/WebSocket\nRequest for Bi-Directional messaging ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "HyZDezM3114Ng_CF2xclF",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -531.6451011032296,
      "y": -274.50582838356456,
      "width": 625.5810546875,
      "height": 210.3307970222357,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2d",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 390095684,
      "version": 685,
      "versionNonce": 466604867,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769964291491,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Messaging Platform - \nMost of users can use mobile/web app\nFor messaging so we can accordingly\nThink of paginate( fixed amount of\nmessages to load ) strategy ",
      "fontSize": 33.652927523557715,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Messaging Platform - \nMost of users can use mobile/web app\nFor messaging so we can accordingly\nThink of paginate( fixed amount of\nmessages to load ) strategy ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pcptQjpJyquS4vwrFWcgf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1054.0794763455256,
      "y": 419.38890988503533,
      "width": 1171.5841194231177,
      "height": 424.3785461788041,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2e",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 125871812,
      "version": 1582,
      "versionNonce": 2047439912,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770011792911,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Server -\n1) Each server can hold connections of many users,\nupon receiving any message server has hash table\nWith User ID (Key) and Connection Obj (Value)\nSo we do lookup on table to find receiver's connection obj\nAnd sends the message to another user.\n2) these servers is also responsible to broadcast online/offline status\nof users and other servers will process the broadcast based on\nfriend list when client starts the app\n/when one user tries to send message to the other user.",
      "fontSize": 33.950283694304325,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Server -\n1) Each server can hold connections of many users,\nupon receiving any message server has hash table\nWith User ID (Key) and Connection Obj (Value)\nSo we do lookup on table to find receiver's connection obj\nAnd sends the message to another user.\n2) these servers is also responsible to broadcast online/offline status\nof users and other servers will process the broadcast based on\nfriend list when client starts the app\n/when one user tries to send message to the other user.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9j2kVcIKsTBuCUReXdO_w",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 313.5594038046954,
      "y": -313.4377983908275,
      "width": 815.2615966796875,
      "height": 161.1506529267764,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2f",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 358608636,
      "version": 860,
      "versionNonce": 1961102067,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770024393205,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Load Balancer -\nThe primary function of this LB/Software is to\nRoute each user to appropriate server connection,\nsince users connections can be on different servers.",
      "fontSize": 32.230130585355276,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Load Balancer -\nThe primary function of this LB/Software is to\nRoute each user to appropriate server connection,\nsince users connections can be on different servers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "NVy3UDXsj6GzClU6yd7ul",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -578.1361393988652,
      "y": 461.58870922665915,
      "width": 1069.0811767578125,
      "height": 588.2958392569412,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2h",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1676409980,
      "version": 1490,
      "versionNonce": 2076597243,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770008783054,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Database -\nHere we will be using HBASE wide column database\nHBASE can support huge number of small writes/Reads\nWith the help of memory buffer reads/writes become efficient.\n\nPartitioning -\n1) we can apply physical & logical partitioning principle.\n2) We can create multiple fix size of shards and map it to \nfew physical servers.\n3) We can create config file/table to re-map shards to different \nphysical servers with growing traffic.\n4) we will use hash(user ID) % shard_number to compute the\nShard ( shard 0, 1, 2 etc) to save/retrieve data.\n",
      "fontSize": 33.61690510039664,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Database -\nHere we will be using HBASE wide column database\nHBASE can support huge number of small writes/Reads\nWith the help of memory buffer reads/writes become efficient.\n\nPartitioning -\n1) we can apply physical & logical partitioning principle.\n2) We can create multiple fix size of shards and map it to \nfew physical servers.\n3) We can create config file/table to re-map shards to different \nphysical servers with growing traffic.\n4) we will use hash(user ID) % shard_number to compute the\nShard ( shard 0, 1, 2 etc) to save/retrieve data.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "OupZFKCQuQEs8WyZeWhSt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -532.6072731467945,
      "y": -488.4812166088204,
      "width": 874.8591064652305,
      "height": 110.77528430147112,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
